# .goosehints – Befit

# High-level guidance for Goose when working in this repository.

project:
  name: Befit
  description: >
    A Goose-powered, multimodal wellness assistant that helps women and caregivers
    turn what they have at home into simple, safe daily actions.

entry_points:
  - AGENTS.md
  - skills/ # if applicable 
  - befit_scan_and_plan.yaml # recipe for scanning pantry/med cabinet and generating a wellness plan
  - DECISIONS.md
  - RISK_LOG.md
  - EVIDENCE_LOG.md
  - LIMITATIONS.md

preferences:
  # Always understand the agent team before proposing workflows.
  - "Read AGENTS.md before designing or modifying agent orchestration."
  - "Prefer using existing recipes (YAML files) and where relevant skills in the skills/ directory over ad-hoc prompting."
  - "Respect and consult RISK_LOG.md and any LIMITATIONS.md when generating health-related outputs."

logging_and_docs:
  - "When asked to update documentation, prefer appending to existing logs (RISK_LOG.md, EVIDENCE_LOG.md, DECISIONS.md) rather than rewriting history."
  - "When proposing code changes that affect agents, recipes or skills, also suggest updates to AGENTS.md, recipes and related SKILL.md files."

safety:
  - "Do not generate medical diagnoses or dosing instructions."
  - "Always include clear disclaimers and limitations for user-facing wellness guidance."
  - "When uncertain about safety, recommend consulting a qualified healthcare professional."

skills:
  # Hints about important skills to use first.
  - "For image or live video frame understanding and pantry/med cabinet analysis, use Befit perception-related skills in skills/befit-* before inventing new workflows."
  - "For updating logs and evidence, use dev-logging skills if present instead of writing free-form notes."

agents:
  # Hints about collaboration style.
  - "Use the Befit Planner agent to coordinate sub-agents (Vision Interpreter, Context Interpreter, Risk Checker, Plan Writer, Reflector) in a hierarchical fashion."
  - "Apply reflection as a distinct step before finalizing user-facing outputs."

ux: 
  # Hints about user interaction and accessibility.
  - "Design Befit as a responsive, mobile-first web app with accessible UI (large tap targets, clear contrast, screen-reader-friendly markup)."
  - “Prefer voice-first interaction (mic button, STT, optional TTS) with photo/upload as fallback.”
mcp:
  # Future MCP App and MCP tool integration.
  - "If MCP tools or MCP Apps are present, prefer using them via established skills or recipes rather than direct, undocumented calls."
